31 Emergency clause. In view of the emergency cited in the preamble, this legislation
42 takes effect when approved.
5 SUMMARY
66 This resolve requires that, by December 31, 2025, the Department of Health and
77 Human Services issue 2 requests for proposals for pilot programs to develop child assertive
88 community treatment teams to serve the Lewiston and Bangor geographic areas. The
99 request for proposals must require the awardees of the grants to use workforce incentives
1100 designed to attract, train and retain child assertive community treatment team staff. The
1111 department is required to engage in a competitive process to determine the awardees. The
1122 awardees for each grant may be, but are not required to be, the same entity. The resolve
1133 also provides one-time funding to provide 2 grants of $160,000 each for the 2 pilot
1144 programs. Within 90 days following the conclusion of the pilot programs, the department
1155 must submit a report to the joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction
1166 over health and human services matters describing the outcomes and recommendations for
1177 continuation of the pilot programs.
